Structured Logging Keys

uses a Mapped Diagnostic Context (MDC) to generate structured logs in a JSON format. The output is a nested group of key-value pairs. You can access data from your structured logs by calling on the keys described on this page.

Most values in the log are strings. Other JSON types such as arrays and integers are used for some nested keys.

In 4.23.2+, you can create a custom metadata file that controls exactly which keys appears in your s. For more information, see Custom and Private Data in [%=General.StructuredLog%]s.

System keys

The following keys can appear in all structured logs, regardless of which command the log originates from:

Key Description
class Java class associated with log event
changelog Name of the associated with the log event
changesetAuthor Value of --author. Author of the being logged
changesetCount Number of s associated with the log event
changesetId Value of --id. ID of the being logged
changesetOutcome Outcome of deploying this
deploymentId ID of database deployment. Appears in all logs in 4.25.0+.
deploymentOutcome Outcome of the database deployment. Appears in all logs in 4.25.0+.
deploymentOutcomeCount Number of s deployed. Appears in all logs in 4.25.0+.
level Value of --log-level. Level of detail of the output.
liquibaseInternalCommand Name of the internal operation
liquibaseCatalogName Value of --liquibase-catalog-name. Name of the database catalog. Appears in all logs in 4.25.0+.
liquibaseCommandName Name of the command entered in the CLI
liquibaseSchemaName Value of --liquibase-schema-name. Name of the database schema. Appears in all logs in 4.25.0+.
liquibaseSystemName System name running
liquibaseSystemUser Name of user running
liquibaseTargetUrl URL of the target database associated with the log
liquibaseVersion Version of installed
message Short descriptor of log event
operationStart UTC timestamp of operation start
operationStop UTC timestamp of operation end
rowsAffected Number of rows in a table the change affects
thread Thread being used
timestamp UTC timestamp of log event

Key Description

changelogSyncOutcome Whether the sync was executed or failed
changesetSyncCount Number of s added to the table
changesetFilepath Path to . Repeats in every log message
changesetContext Context applied to . Repeats in every log message
changesetLabel Label applied to . Repeats in every log message
changesetOperationStart UTC timestamp of operation start. Repeats in every log message
changesetOperationStop UTC timestamp of operation end. Repeats in every log message
changesetSyncOutcome Outcome of sync. Repeats in every log message
databaseChangelogSql SQL to update the [%=General.databasechangelog%] table
databaseChangelogTableOutcome Outcome of update to the table

checks run

In 4.25.1+, the checks run output delivers an expansive log of Policy Checks that can run against s and databases. This allows you to dive deep into what policy checks are run, if they are customized, and more.

Keys that can appear in a checks run :

Top-level keys

Key Description
changelogChecks The checks that run against the
databaseChecks The checks that run against the database

Key Description

integration integrated checks
